column2: # Read the data from published CSV file into a data frame.
# Rename the variables of music_data frame and print the five rows of your data
"How often do you listen to music on a daily basis?" = 3,
"What are your favorite genres of music?" = 4,
"If you had to choose your top 3 favorite types of music, what would they be?" = 5,
"How is music important in your life? Please type between 1 to 10." = 6,
"In what ways do you listen to music?" = 7,

"How much do you think about the reasonable price of music streaming services per week? Please type a numeric value only." = 8) %>% select("How old are you?", "How often do you listen to music on a daily basis?", "What are your favorite genres of music?", "If you had to choose your top 3 favorite types of music, what would they be?", "How is music important in your life? Please type between 1 to 10.", "In what ways do you listen to music?", "How much do you think about the reasonable price of music streaming services per week? Please type a numeric value only.") %>% slice(c(3, 5, 8, 10, 30))
